# WebVitals.io Development Rules for AWS Kiro IDE

## Project Context
- Name: WebVitals.io
- Type: Full-Stack SaaS (Next.js + Node.js + PostgreSQL)
- Timeline: 4 weeks
- AWS Integration: Yes (CodeCommit, CodePipeline, EC2, RDS)

## Kiro IDE Instructions
1. Auto-push all commits to AWS CodeCommit
2. Trigger CodePipeline on each push
3. Deploy to EC2 instance on main branch
4. Use RDS for PostgreSQL (not local)
5. Store secrets in AWS Secrets Manager

## Development Process
- Follow PRD in /docs/PRD.md exactly
- Use Amazon Q (Kiro's AI) for code generation
- Each milestone generates one set of commits
- All commits auto-push to CodeCommit

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Next.js 15, React 19, TypeScript, Redux, Recharts, Tailwind
- Backend: Node.js 20, Express, TypeScript, Prisma, PostgreSQL
- AWS: CodeCommit, CodePipeline, CodeBuild, EC2, RDS, Secrets Manager
- Testing: Jest, Supertest

## AWS Infrastructure
- RDS PostgreSQL: Auto-provisioned
- EC2 Instance: t3.micro (free tier eligible)
- CodeCommit: Git repository
- CodePipeline: Auto-triggered on push
- Secrets Manager: Store API keys, DB passwords
